<h1>About This App</h1>

<h2>What is this?</h2>
<p>
  This application uses data pulled from the Comic Vine API to let you
  browse publishers, comic series (volumes), individual issues, and characters
  from across the history of comics.
</p>

<h2>Data Sources</h2>
<li><h4>Comic Vine API</h4></li>
<p>
  The primary data source is the <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/">Comic Vine API</a>,
  a comprehensive database of comic book information. Data is pulled from four
  endpoints — publishers, volumes, issues, and characters — and stored across
  five related database tables.
</p>

<li><h4>Faker Gem</h4></li>
<p>
  User reviews attached to individual issues are generated using the Faker gem,
  simulating reader ratings and comments with randomized names, ratings, and review text.
</p>

<h2>Data Structure</h2>
<p>
  Publishers produce many Volumes (comic series). Each Volume contains many Issues.
  Characters appear across many Issues, forming a many-to-many relationship.
  Each Issue can also have many user Reviews.
</p>